{{Mammals by population sidebar}} This is a collection of lists of mammal species by the estimated global population, divided by [[mammal classification|orders]]. (Lists only exist for some orders; e.g. the most diverse order - [[rodent]]s - is missing.) Much of the data in these lists were created by the [[International Union for Conservation of Nature|IUCN]]'s Global Mammal Assessment Team, which consists of 1700 [[mammalogy|mammalogists]] from over 130 countries. They recognize 5488 species in the class.<ref name="IUCN Mammals intro">{{cite web |url= http://www.iucnredlist.org/initiatives/mammals |title= Initiatives:Mammals |accessdate= 2012-11-21 |author= IUCN |date= n.d. |work= IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2012.2 |publisher= [[IUCN]]}}</ref><ref name="IUCN Mammals acknowledgements">{{cite web |url= http://www.iucnredlist.org/initiatives/mammals/acknowledgements |title= Initiatives:Mammals:Acknowledgements |accessdate= 2012-11-21 |author= IUCN |date= n.d. |work= IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2012.2 |publisher= [[IUCN]]}}</ref>
These lists are not comprehensive, as not all mammals have had their numbers estimated. For example, a live specimen of the [[spade-toothed whale]] was first observed in December 2010, and the event only recognized as such in November 2012; no estimate yet exists for the global population.<ref name="Thompson et al">{{cite journal |last=Thompson |first=Kirsten |author2=C. Scott Baker |author3=Anton van Helden |author4=Selina Patel |author5=Craig Miller |author6=Rochelle Constantine |title=The world's rarest whale |journal=[[Current Biology]] |date=6 November 2012 |volume=22 |issue=21 |pages=R905–R906 |url=http://www.cell.com/current-biology/retrieve/pii/S0960982212010597 |doi=10.1016/j.cub.2012.08.055 |accessdate=7 November 2012}}</ref> The accuracy of the quote numbers may only be an [[order of magnitude]].
It is estimated that the total number of wild mammals in the world is about 130 [[1,000,000,000|billion]].<ref>http://reducing-suffering.org/how-many-wild-animals-are-there/</ref>
==Lists by taxonomic order== *[[List of even-toed ungulates by population]] - cattle, sheep, pigs, goats, water buffalo, camels, bison, yak, llamas, deer, antelope, giraffe, moose, hippos *[[List of odd-toed ungulates by population]] - horses, donkeys, mules, zebras, asses, rhinos, tapirs *[[List of carnivorans by population]] - domestic and wild cats & dogs, seals & other sea mammals, bears, weasels, foxes, mongoose *[[List of bats by population]] *[[List of cetacean species]] with population estimates - dolphins, porpoises, whales *[[List of primates by population]] - humans, other apes (including chimpanzees), monkeys
